<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-10T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-10T22:00:00-05:00" n="592" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P. W/974: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-11T10:00:00+07:00">December
                                    11, 1941—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 5:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>485. By proclamation dated December 9th the National Government of China
                            “formally declares war on Japan” and by separate proclamation same date
                            declares that “a state of war exists” between China and Germany and
                            Italy “as from midnight December 9”.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>